# Docker Development Environment

## Services Configuration
- **WordPress**: Latest version on port 8000
- **MySQL 8.0**: Database server
- **WP CLI**: Command-line WordPress management

## Key Files
- **Docker Compose**: [docker-compose.yml](mdc:docker-compose.yml) - Service orchestration
- **Setup Script**: [wp-cli-setup.sh](mdc:wp-cli-setup.sh) - WordPress initialization
- **Start Script**: [start.sh](mdc:start.sh) - Quick start helper

## Environment Variables
```yaml
# Database
MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD: rootpassword
MYSQL_DATABASE: wordpress
MYSQL_USER: wordpress
MYSQL_PASSWORD: wordpress_password

# WordPress
WORDPRESS_DB_HOST: db:3306
WORDPRESS_DEBUG: 1
WP_HOME: http://localhost:8000
WP_SITEURL: http://localhost:8000
```

## Development Commands
```bash
# Start services
docker-compose up -d

# View logs
docker-compose logs -f wp-cli

# Access WordPress container
docker-compose exec wordpress bash

# WP CLI commands
docker-compose exec wp-cli wp --help --allow-root

# Stop services
docker-compose down

# Remove everything (including data)
docker-compose down -v
```

## Volume Mappings
- **WordPress Data**: `wordpress_data:/var/www/html`
- **Themes**: `./themes:/var/www/html/wp-content/themes`
- **Plugins**: `./plugins:/var/www/html/wp-content/plugins`
- **Uploads**: `./uploads:/var/www/html/wp-content/uploads`

## WordPress Admin Access
- **URL**: http://localhost:8000/wp-admin
- **Username**: admin
- **Password**: admin123

## Troubleshooting
- **Port conflicts**: Change port in docker-compose.yml
- **Database issues**: Restart db service
- **Permissions**: Use [scripts/docker-fix-permissions.sh](mdc:scripts/docker-fix-permissions.sh)
- **WP CLI issues**: Re-run setup script
